Please be aware this spec file is based on the original spec file that nginx provides in their source rpm packages.

You can build the rpms by running the build script: ./build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-or-mainline-modules.sh stable headers-more

First input should be the nginx version so for example “stable” or “mainline”.
Second input should be the module name for example “headers-more”

So you can build a module rpm as following:

headers-more module for stable nginx:
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ulyaoth/repository/master/ulyaoth-nginx-modules/build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-or-mainline-modules.sh ; chmod +x build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-or-mainline-modules.sh ; ./build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-or-mainline-modules.sh stable headers-more


headers-more module for mainline nginx:
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ulyaoth/repository/master/ulyaoth-nginx-modules/build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-or-mainline-modules.sh ; chmod +x build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-or-mainline-modules.sh ; ./build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-or-mainline-modules.sh mainline headers-more


Supported modules:
headers-more (https://github.com/openresty/headers-more-nginx-module)
echo (https://github.com/openresty/echo-nginx-module)
pam (https://github.com/stogh/ngx_http_auth_pam_module)
form-input (https://github.com/calio/form-input-nginx-module)
devel-kit (https://github.com/simpl/ngx_devel_kit)
encrypted-session (https://github.com/openresty/encrypted-session-nginx-module)
array-var (https://github.com/openresty/array-var-nginx-module)
